  ===========================================================
CRC stands for CodeReady Containers, which is a tool provided by Red Hat to help developers run a local OpenShift cluster on their personal machines.
Itâ€™s primarily designed for developers who want to test, experiment, and develop applications for OpenShift without needing a full-fledged OpenShift 
cluster hosted in the cloud or on-premises.

A pull secret is basically a JSON file that contains credentials used to authenticate against Red Hatâ€™s container image registry (registry.redhat.io).
OpenShift uses this registry to pull the official Red Hat container images (like the cluster components, operators, and more). Without the pull secret,
OpenShift wonâ€™t be able to download these images.

